caption: Its rare that I give 5 stars but, this place here.... Oh my heavenly stars, they showed out with this here sub! Its was so good, I almost liked the foil!!!! I eat at the same place (just a different location) and they sho nuff know what the heck they are doing! 😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍
Ambiance and Selection is Superb! Food Smelled Amazing! Cool Hip Area and Tables & Chairs Inside and Out! Can't Wait To Come Back!
Great italian style deli. Less grocery items than the other location, but the food is just the same. The "small" steak sub must have over a pound of meat on it.
Absolutely Delish! Great Costumer Service and Excellent Steak Sandwiches!👍

Love the food here but we won't be coming back for a while, if at all. Not a single employee wearing their mask properly...the person at the front register didn't even have their mouth covered. At this point there's no excuse.
Very nice food

We had planned on getting a treat st Bone's (next door) than head in for a sandwich to take home. We parked in there lot considering our plan. We got out of the car and was met with an employee standing in front of the restaurant screaming at us that we couldn't park there. He paced as we juggled dogs and got keys. He countined to yell at us. My partner asked him to stop yelling at her and stated she is a women, stop calling me buddy. Despite her request, he countined. He then countined to pace and stare at us through the window. Needless to say - we made our stop at Bone's after moving our car, but did not order and never will. Wish I could give zero stars. Absolutely unnecessary and very rude. A simple conversation could have saved this interaction and this awful review.
Amazing food and a great price.  No surprise they have 3 stores... top notch!

Always fantastic! Value and staff are always will to help in choosing something especially if you're extremely indecisive such as myself... I definitely recommend allowing them to do what they do and be creative with  your meal... they won't disappoint. 100/100
Not as good as the Calabresellas on Buffalo Rd
Their subs are delicious and very filling.  Friendly staff too.
Tremendous Philly cheesesteak. Every sub made with care. 10/10

Authentic Italian Deli with all the old world Italian  meats and products!   Deli is very clean with a nice seating area and large windows to view all the action on Park Ave and Goodman.  Across from Parkleigh.     Delicious subs and wraps with generous tasty fixings.  A variety of tasty coffee and  desserts.  A cute, quaint and scrumptious deli with friendly staff in a great neighborhood.  Try it, you'll be back
Generous portions and fresh bread. Need to try more of these subs!
Wonderful Park Avenue Italian deli.
Best  place  in Rochester for a sub! Not only is the food fantastic, but all of the staff makes it that more special!
Food is amazing . VERY CLEAN environment and the staff are just the greatest.  Very friendly, outgoing, SEXY & WELCOMING 🤷‍♂️👌😆
Excellent bread

I went in recently with the full intent to get something like an Italian assorted. However, upon entering, a blackboard changed my fate by announcing a hot pastrami special with pickles Swiss thousand island... Oh yeah. So I ordered this and it was fantastic, the smallest size available fed me three meals. Can't wait to return. On a previous visit, I did in fact get a sandwich with assorted cold cuts. there didn't seem to be any option as to what toppings I wanted when I ordered, but their choices worked out fine.

Guy behind the counter recommended the dominator. Highlighting how the turkey was cooked and what other ingredients are typically on the sub. What he failed to mention was that the entire sub was doused in hot sauce. Long story short after eating a few bites I vomited due to the absurd amount of heat.

Their large subs can easily feed two people and are practically overloaded with meat, but they still use high-quality ingredients and their sub rolls are substantial and delicious to match. They also have a great selection of Local, Italian, and classic NY Deli specialties (Sauces, imported tomatoes, Spiedie Chips!) and tons of baked goods or desert options. They do a great job of following the current COVID Guidelines and I haven't seen any change in quality since it has started.  This is one of the most welcoming businesses I've been to in Roc and it's obvious every person behind the counter puts a lot of care into what they do. They are proud of the product they put out and will make sure you are happy. All of this at a price of ~$11 a sub, it's such an amazing value and we're lucky to have them here!
Had the most AMAZING Cold Roast Beef Sub today...possibly the best ever. Rare, tender, and deeeelish. What a gem on Park Ave.
(Translated by Google) The service was excellent  (Original) 素晴らしいサービスでした
Amazing food and customer service Grubhub driver messed up and one of the  employees personally brought out the missing item!!!! All around great place highly recommend!!!
Not only do they have the freshest food but their service is A1 ! Get the steak sub, You’ll be happy :)
Wonderful discovery downtown, about a mile from where I currently reside. I have had takeout and delivery thi week and I’m for sure going back again soon. Grubhub Delivery was fast and delicious.

My family and I all agree, that Calabresella’s sandwiches are absolutely amazing! The owner and his wife are extremely friendly and welcoming. Their Italian cookies were a hit at my daughter’s birthday party!

Was visiting town with fiancé and dropped in whilst searching for a light breakfast snack. The fellow at the front recommended the 8 inch breakfast sub, which I got. It was a bit heftier of a meal than I was initially looking for, but it was, without question, the best breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had. This was not a casually slapped-together ‘wich; the egg, cheese, and bacon was mixed together into a seamless whole. Definitely worth a try if you’re looking for a step up from from your regular breakfast sandwich!

This is a fantastic sub shop and deli! I came in and ordered a fried bologna sub and added on some soppressata salmi, which i highly recommend trying. Will grilled it up for me and took the time to really make sure everything was perfect. The sub was delicious, however, the one thing I would like to recommend is adding Uncle Ralph’s Magic Sauce on top. Also, recommend you start carrying a stock of Uncle Ralph’s for the people to purchase. You won’t regret it!
Super friendly staff and really tasty sandwiches.

Decided to try them yesterday for the first time because I NEEDED a sub and Rubino's was closed at 2pm. Placed a takeout order 30 minutes before they closed (usually restaurants hate this). The owner personally prepared both of our subs as if he were making them for his best friends--jam packed and weighing in at a few pounds each. He took the time to talk with myself and other customers, again as if we were his best friends. The whole time, making sure we knew how appreciative and happy he was to have our business. Subs were excellent and we'll be going back soon.

So many delicious sounding options! I wanted to buy one of everything when I got to the store to pickup my online order. Their sandwiches are fantastic (and built well!!) so I fully intend on coming back. Hopefully next time I can get some bakery goodies or something!
Friendly and fun, and all of the food is amazing, but really I’m in love with their chicken salad. It’s rich and delicious and satisfying. This eatery is worth a visit.
Wonderful staff and delicious food!
The subs are my favorite in the city and the staff and owner are super friendly. I HIGHLY recommend this place.
Excellent....
You will not be disappointed with the experience of this old world deli in a perfect location

I’m from philly and I think it’s an accurate representation of a cheesesteak if you call and ask for american cheese and fries onions. Only thing I would say is a little less meat more emphasis on the melted cheese that’s what brings it all together. And then fry the onions a little more and it will be perfect!  Super nice owner too!
Very gentle people and nice sub

This is my go-to for lunch! The staff is always so friendly and engaging. Love that they feature items from other local businesses as well. Definitely check them out if you haven’t already! (& try the pasta salad 😋)

Will the owner is an awesome guy. If you ever get the chance to chat with him I would. The food is great and the subs are stuffed. Check out the Italian ice as well. If your looking to make your own they sell top quality meat and have great pickles for sell too.
Super friendly Fast service...

Great subs but seems no customer distancing in any way also one employee not wearing a mask was going to say something but the owner wasn't wearing one either having it around your neck doesn't cut it

I get 1-2 subs a week here. They are consistently great. Even dibellas subs taste like a gas station sub compared to calabresella's. Deli salads, coffee, baked goods are all great too. Friendly staff, clean store.
5 stars all around great service and one of my favorite subs

Colon kicker is their best sub by far. They always give you generous portions. Subs made with fresh baked bread and fresh ingredients consistently. You can really tell quality goes into every order they get. Seriously, you won’t regret trying their colon kicker sub!
These subs will give Wegmans and DiBellas a run for their money. Their Prosciutto sub is AMAZING. They have homemade cannolis and one of the only places to get eight o'clock coffee

Sub shop is ok not great.  Bread is ordinary . It's better at dibellas and Wegmans.  Staff is not attentive at all.  I've been there three times and they have never greeted me or acknowledged my presence.  Leave me hanging at the counter waiting for them to finish what they are doing.
Awesome food! Great staff!

What a great experience.  The food is good, the helpings are enormous and the coffee is not weak.  Best of all the service is terrific.  They listen, they chat and they have a great sense of humor.  And yes, it's clean everywhere.  Lastly, instead of using plastic for your take home they provide tin foil.
Amazing food. I can't compliment the staff enough; they are all very chill and nice people.
Amazing peeps, great food, please don't hesitate, just go!!!!!
Great subs, excellent customer service!  Love the meat ball sub, really good bread too.
Best subs ever good people good service
Lots of meats in the sandwich for the price. Great staff
Best sandwiches in the area. Beware that Large means LARGE! Great value for their portions and everything is very fresh.

This the best sub place ever! Never really had a good sub until I came to this place. The place is clean inside and out. friendly courteous people that actually listen to what you want on your sub and for your food. Always shop and eat local. Thank you for delicious subs always! :) Never not once disappointed. I will always tell people to come  to Calabresella's sub shop! They also have delicious chips.
Excellent Italian Deli (Classic Style).  Giant subs. Staff is awesome and friendly.  Highly recommend !!!
An amazing little deli, corner store that makes amazing sandwiches has cheesy Eddie's desserts and the staff is pretty cool I would eat here again.
Sandwiches were awesome. Filling and well made. Lots of other great sandwich options.
Among the best sandwich places I have been! Corn beef amazing, great portions!

I make it a point to try cheese steak subs/sandwiches where ever I go. I have been doing this for the past 25 years or so. I have even had several in Philly. They all got left in the dust when I ordered the shaved steak sub at Calabresella's. This was by far, the best steak sub I've ever tasted. Unbelievable!! I will be going back soon to have the hot pastrami!! Can't wait.

Best subs in town bar none. They're so big you can barely bite into it you literally have to eat it in sections lol....Plus the staff is the nicest group of people I've ever meet in my life no exaggeration and thats because they understand how a business should be run. I had a 12 sub order a half hour before they closed and they took the order no problem and they did it with a smile AND THEN THANKED ME!!! for the business. If that was any other sub shop in Rochester they would have been miserable af or turned me down, I've dealt with it before, trust me on this place, GO HERE!!! Well done Calabresella's keep up the great work!  P.S...I get the steak sub everytime it's absolutely amazing
Delicious, large serving subs.

What a great lunch spot! The shaved steak sandwich is to die for. Thought we'd try out the Park Ave location and was just as delish as their Gates store   without the gourmet grocery. Try it out, you won't be disappointed.
Service was great and the place was clean and welcoming. My wife and I didn't like their shaved steak sandwich at all. This is pretty subjective, obviously.
Amazing people, awesome environment, extremely clean. Food was absolutely delicious. These guys are the best around by far!
Holy Cow the steak and cheese bomber was GREAT!

First time here today. Such a long wait for two subs and over priced for a basic cold sub. It was super hot inside because of all the windows and sun shining right in, they unfortunately messed up my order but were prompt about fixing it. My boyfriend really enjoyed the meatball sub. Props to them for starting a sub shop with dibellas right down the road.
The chicken salad was delicious and the staff was great. More of a pick up place but enough seating for a quick bite while on lunch
Food was very good, but I was charged higher priced than what was posted on the board and printed in the menu.
I had a meatball sub it was outstanding, can't wait to try something else to see how it is

Didn't know it changed hands until I parked. All the flavors they had for coffee, along with the baked goods, were gone with the last tenants. The new shop's salads, breads, & other lunchfare would have tempted me if I'd been looking for more than coffee.
Pretty convincing argument for the best subs in Rochester
A nice local alternative to Wegmans! Subs are big, salads are homemade, and staff is friendly.
Great Italian Assorted!
The Dominator is amazing, this is my favorite place for subs around, the bread is always fresh and taste fantastic, the staff was very nice and helpful, definitely will be a return customer!
FINALLY! A Real Italian Sub Shop on Park Ave!!!
I had meatball sub. Food was nice and hot. Really good. Great selection of sandwiches.
Great food
Loved the new place at Goodman and Park. Excellent food and prices with great service
Really great steak eggs & cheese breakfast sub, great corner location with minimal outside seating. Oui chef.
Great sandwich, friendly people.
Best sub shop in Rochester! Not the cheapest but definitely worth it!!!
Good subs
I purchased The Dominator sandwich. It was fantastic. Plenty of Turkey smothered in chicken wing sauce. Yum! I will definitely visit them again.
My favorite sub stop both locations.  Fantastic sandwiches and service.
Best steak sub in the Rochester area. By far.
If you want to be in a delicious food coma then this is the place for you! Nice clean and open atmosphere with alot of selection and choices in subs.
Everything is delicious.  Like to the point of not being able to decide what to order!
Large sandwiches, taste very good and friendly staff
The best place to buy subs from. They taste amazing including the roll. They take pride in making their subs, they layer the toppings in. So many toppings and meat.
Everyone who was working that day was really nice and helpful, and the pastrami sub was DELICIOUS
Love this place. Great food and friendly employees
Great old school Italian deli !! Reminds me of back home
